#. type: Title ###
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:52
#, no-wrap
msgid "New Zealand"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:55
#, no-wrap
msgid "**9 JULY | Canterbury, New Zealand**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:57
msgid "![Rebels dressed as cows](/assets/uploads/pic3.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:59
msgid ""
"The giant global dairy corporation "
"[Fonterra](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fonterra) was greeted with [drums, "
"cow costumes, placards and a pile of "
"coal](https://www.facebook.com/XR.Chch/videos/1468110950055597/), as "
"Extinction Rebellion Ōtautahi (Christchurch) asked the question, Why are "
"Fonterra still using coal in a climate emergency?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:61
msgid ""
"[Fonterra](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fonterra) is responsible for "
"approximately 30% of the world's dairy exports. A cooperative owned by "
"10,500 New Zealand farmers, it is New Zealand’s largest company."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:63
msgid ""
"The demonstration follows Bathurst Resources’ application to expand the "
"Canterbury coal mine, with most of its coal going to Fonterra’s nearby "
"factory to dehydrate milk."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:65
msgid ""
"An [XR Ōtautahi](https://www.facebook.com/XR.Chch/) spokesperson said: “The "
"proposed expansion of the Canterbury coal mine has everything to do with "
"[Fonterra’s addiction to "
"coal.](https://thedailyblog.co.nz/2020/07/10/fonterra-milk-and-coal-dont-mix-extinction-rebellion/) "
"They are burning coal to dry out milk. Why are we seeing these irresponsible "
"decisions in the middle of a climate crisis?”"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:66
#, no-wrap
msgid "Europe 1"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:69
msgid ""
"Groups of rebels from all over Europe mobilised from June 29 to July 3 to "
"denounce the aberrations of a system which destroys the conditions of our "
"lives a little more every day. This first Europe-wide campaign enabled many "
"countries to unite their voices to express the same message: instead of "
"industries, **it’s the planet that needs a recovery plan.**"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:71
msgid "![\"Bail Out The Planet\" XR Poster](/assets/uploads/pic11.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:73
#, no-wrap
msgid "**4 JULY | Tours, France**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:75
msgid "![French rebels demonstrating](/assets/uploads/pic10.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:77
msgid ""
"Rebels protested against the millions of euros in bailouts granted by the "
"French government to low-cost airlines. The woman’s placard compared the "
"30-euro price of a 1015-kilometre flight from Tours airport to Porto in "
"Portugal with the same price for a train ticket from Tours to Paris (240km)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:79
#, no-wrap
msgid "**30 JUNE | Paris, France**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:81
msgid ""
"![French rebels, almost nude, wtih a large puddle of fake blood in "
"front](/assets/uploads/pic5.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:83
msgid ""
"French rebels [stripped to their underwear and poured "
"‘blood’](https://www.facebook.com/xrfrance/videos/581976525837039/) outside "
"the French Ministry of Economy and Finance. Their goal: to ‘point the "
"finger’ at political leaders injecting billions into a deadly ‘revival’ of "
"the old normality instead of investing in the climate, biodiversity and "
"other vital needs such as health, food security and employment. Seven rebels "
"were arrested."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:85
#, no-wrap
msgid "**2 JULY | Helsinki, Finland**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:87
msgid "![Finnish rebels laying down in the street](/assets/uploads/pic19.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:89
msgid ""
"Finnish rebels lay down in the street to block the cars of government "
"ministers from entering the Senate building. They were demanding that "
"politicians recognise that the economy can no longer be run as it was before "
"the Covid-19 "
"crisis.[](https://twitter.com/hashtag/BailOutThePlanet?src=hashtag_click)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:91
#, no-wrap
msgid "**2 JUL | Berlin, Germany**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:93
msgid ""
"Berlin rebels [entered Germany’s "
"parliament](https://twitter.com/XRBerlin/status/1278613793090699264) to "
"protest a disastrous new law that would allow coal to be burned until 2039 - "
"far too long if the country is to meet its Paris Agreement commitments."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:95
msgid ""
"Rebels let it rain with leaflets and told the startled MPs that a citizens’ "
"assembly was needed to take the necessary steps to tackle the climate "
"crisis. The politicians ratified the new law anyway. As well as setting a "
"phase-out deadline a decade too late, the law [pledges €4.35 billion in "
"compensation](https://www.euractiv.com/section/climate-environment/opinion/new-coal-law-will-be-canary-in-a-coal-mine-moment-for-german-presidency/) "
"for the coal industry. Germany holds the EU presidency and is the 4th "
"largest CO2 emitter in the world - its cosy attitude to coal sets a terrible "
"example."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:97
msgid "![Rebels dressed as spacemen demonstrating](/assets/uploads/pic14.png)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:99
msgid "Space age rebels protest the coal law after it was passed by parliament."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:101
#, no-wrap
msgid "**3 JULY | Munich, Germany**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:103
msgid ""
"![German rebels winding green thread around an "
"entrance](/assets/uploads/pic12.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:105
msgid ""
"Rebels wound 4 km of green thread between two columns at the entrance to the "
"Munich offices of the European Commission to draw attention to the fact that "
"the supposed [European Green "
"Deal](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cBU48JHJ-4M) is not very green at all "
"and current EU climate policy is leading to disaster."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:107
#, no-wrap
msgid "**4 JULY | Budapest, Hungary**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:109
msgid "![Hungarian rebels demonstrating.](/assets/uploads/pic6.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:111
#, no-wrap
msgid "*‘A Lifebelt for the Planet.’ Photo: Czele Annamária.*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:113
msgid ""
"As part of the Europe-wide actions, Hungarian rebels demonstrated in front "
"of the Ministry of Finance. “Our governments provide unconditional support "
"to save polluting industries such as the automotive industry or aviation. We "
"demand that the Hungarian government focus on providing human needs such as "
"health, food supply and the environment,” they said."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:115
#, no-wrap
msgid "**29 JUNE | Turin, Italy**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:117
msgid "![Semi-nude rebels protesting outside a bank](/assets/uploads/pic21.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:119
msgid ""
"’Intesa is naked’ read the signs, referring to the Italian bank Intesa "
"SanPaolo. Turin rebels expressed their opposition outside its offices to the "
"restart of the economy at the expense of planetary ecosystems and human "
"lives."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:121
#, no-wrap
msgid "**5 JULY | Palermo, Sicily**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:123
msgid "![Rebels holding up a big rainbow banner](/assets/uploads/pic4.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:125
#, no-wrap
msgid "*‘No Rainbow on a Planet With No Rain’.*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:126
#, no-wrap
msgid "Europe 2"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:129
msgid ""
"More actions took place around Europe before and after the week-long Bail "
"Out The Planet mobilisation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:131
#, no-wrap
msgid "**7 JULY | Baltic pipeline, Denmark**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:133
msgid "![Rebels blocking a construction site](/assets/uploads/pic7.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:135
msgid ""
"Fifteen rebels were arrested when they blocked a construction site for the "
"new [Baltic Pipe](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baltic_Pipe)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:137
msgid ""
"Due for completion in October 2022, the pipeline will carry [natural "
"gas](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natural_gas) from the "
"[Norwegian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Norway) sector of the [North "
"Sea](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_Sea) to "
"[Poland](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poland) via Denmark. The project is "
"being developed by Danish operator "
"[Energinet](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Energinet) and Poland’s "
"[Gaz-System](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gaz-System). It received 215m "
"euros of EU funding in 2019."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:139
#, no-wrap
msgid "**18 JUNE | State Forestry Management Centre, Estonia**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:141
msgid "![Estonian rebels demonstrating](/assets/uploads/pic20.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:143
msgid ""
"About [100 rebels and environmental activists "
"marched](https://www.facebook.com/watch/?v=252483676051498) around the "
"headquarters of Estonia’s State Forestry Management Centre (RMK). They were "
"protesting against the mass clear-cutting of Estonian forests, in spite of "
"warnings from prominent scientists and environmental organisations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:145
msgid ""
"The rebels disobediently planted an oak tree to symbolise the need to care "
"for our forests instead of turning them into quick profits for corrupt "
"institutions. Established in 1999, RMK made a profit of 43.2m euros in 2019 "
"and was one of the top 10 companies in Estonia."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:147
#, no-wrap
msgid "**24 JUNE | Gdansk, Poland**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:149
msgid "![Rebels demonstrating in Poland](/assets/uploads/pic17.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:151
msgid ""
"Rebels outside the Board of Education in Gdańsk. Together with the Polish "
"Youth Climate Strike, they were protesting education material prepared by "
"the Ministry of National Education in which global warming is described as "
"bringing benefits to the planet! Photo: Pamela Gasiorowski."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:153
#, no-wrap
msgid "**27 JUN | Place de l’Europe, Lausanne, Switzerland**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:155
msgid ""
"![Rebels lying \"dead\" in the shape of the XR "
"logo](/assets/uploads/pic13.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:157
msgid ""
"Doctors for XR Switzerland held [a powerful symbolic "
"performance](https://www.facebook.com/doctors4xr.ch/videos/328387768152848/) "
"in Lausanne to highlight [links between ecological catastrophe and human "
"health "
"problems](https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2020/mar/18/tip-of-the-iceberg-is-our-destruction-of-nature-responsible-for-covid-19-aoe?CMP=Share_iOSApp_Other), "
"including the spread of infectious diseases like Covid-19."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:159
msgid ""
"More than 80 medical rebels in white coats and doctors’ paraphernalia "
"gathered at the Place de l’Europe to lead a funeral procession with coffin, "
"skull and stained-glass sand timer before lying down dead in the shape of "
"the XR logo to represent the dangers of [global "
"heating.](https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2020/jul/14/livestock-farming-and-fossil-fuels-could-drive-4c-global-heat-rise?CMP=Share_iOSApp_Other)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:161
#, no-wrap
msgid "**12-21 JUNE | Germany**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:163
msgid "![Rebels dancing on a bridge amongst bubbles](/assets/uploads/pic16.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:165
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Discobedience on the Oberbaum Bridge, Berlin*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:167
msgid ""
"Last month saw XR Germany launch its Rebellion Wave, a 9-day action "
"extravaganza organised by groups across the country. The decentralised wave "
"encompassed both digital and physical disruption. Highlights included "
"blocking access to coal-fired power plants and mass ‘discobedience’ in "
"central Berlin."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:169
msgid "![Rebels blocking access to a power plant](/assets/uploads/pic18.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:171
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*50 rebels block access to the Lippendorf coal-fired power plant near "
"Leipzig.*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:173
#, no-wrap
msgid "**27 JUNE | Prague, Czech Republic**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:175
msgid "![Rebels lying down in a square in Prague](/assets/uploads/pic2.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-xr-unchained-16.md:176
msgid ""
"‘Let’s have a picnic in Prague Castle’. Concluding a series of "
"socially-distanced actions since early May, Czech Republic rebels keep "
"demanding that President Zeman meets with them to discuss the climate "
"crisis."
msgstr ""
